items.title: Countries not doing enough to keep rise in global temperatures under 1.5C, UN says
items.description: The UN's review of national climate plans shows the world is well off track to limit warming

items.title: Fawlty Towers star Prunella Scales dies aged 93
items.description: Scales played hotel manager Sybil Fawlty, the bossy wife of Basil, in the classic British sitcom.

items.title: Two military sites earmarked as asylum seeker accommodation
items.description: Housing asylum seekers in hotels has cost billions, while they have also become a focal point for protests.

items.title: Singer Raye says lost songbooks found ahead of album two
items.description: The star has been on "a rollercoaster journey" after her work was stolen along with her car last year.

items.title: Amazon confirms 14,000 corporate job losses as it focuses on AI
items.description: The company says the opportunities provided by AI means it needs to be "organised more leanly."
